name: MediaType
comment:
A class representing an HTTP media type, as used in Accept and Content-Type headers.

This is immutable; new instances can be created based on an old instance by calling http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.

type.name: type
type.comment: The primary identifier of the MIME type.

subtype.name: subtype
subtype.comment: The secondary identifier of the MIME type.

parameters.name: parameters
parameters.comment:
The parameters to the media type.

This map is immutable.

parse.name: parse
parse.comment:
Parses a media type.

This will throw a FormatError if the media type is invalid.

change.name: change
change.comment:
Returns a copy of this http_parser/http_parser.MediaType with some fields altered.

http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.type and http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.subtype alter the corresponding fields. http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.mimeType is parsed and alters both the http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.type and http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.subtype fields; it cannot be passed along with http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.type or http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.subtype.

http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.parameters overwrites and adds to the corresponding field. If http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.change.clearParameters is passed, it replaces the corresponding field entirely instead.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment:
Converts the media type to a string.

This will produce a valid HTTP media type.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of http_parser/http_parser.MediaType.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
